<div id="content" class="full">
<h1>Research Focus</h1>

<img src="/media/images/lab.png" class="right" alt="Group Photo Here" /><p> 

The Brent lab studies systems biology using both computational and experimental methods. We develop quantitative, kinetic models of signal transduction and regulatory networks. We are doing this at scales ranging from a single biological phenomenon (e.g. regulation of glucose transporters in yeast) to an entire cell.
</p>

<p>

</p>
<p>
Brief research summaries can be found on my
<a href="http://engineering.wustl.edu/facultybio.aspx?faculty=133&department=126">
School of Engineering page</a> and my
<a href="http://www.dbbs.wustl.edu/dbbs/website.nsf/FA/696016B5B07B156586256D4E005B2
CCD?OpenDocument">  Division of Biological and Biomedical Sciences (DBBS)
page</a>.
</p>

